reviews.text: This is an 18th century Roman Catholic mission church. It is one of finest I have been to in the California in terms of history and facts. There is an entry fee of $9 per head (less for children). We found parking easily there. It took us 1 hour to complete it.
Love the history and the architectural work of the place. I've visit here when I was younger and will say different experience now that I enjoy history. Simply beautiful

If you've been wondering how life was 200 years ago, this is where to find a snippet of 1700 life and objects. There's a tour guide here too to explain the different scenes you'd find yourself. It's a place you should visit if you are going to California for pleasure and you love old buildings, whether or not you're a Catholic. I will visit again

Sunday admission is by donation.  There is Sunday mass, so be aware that you can't explore the chapel during those times.  The history was fascinating and the grounds are beautiful.  

Great for anyone with an interest in history,  religion,  or just up for learning something new.  Not great for kids.
Most spectacular of the missions I have visited!!  Lots to see and well worth the admission price ($9.50).  Do not miss the outer museums and cemetery.  Excellent gift shop, too!!

A beautiful spot that's great for hiking, wildlife and wildflower spotting. I was only able to spend an hour here but that was nowhere near enough time to see everything. Allow at least three hours to take full advantage of the reserve if not entering with a car.

There are plenty of opportunities to see wildflowers, sea otters and seals at numerous spots around the coastal area. Highly worth a visit, don't miss this place.

Everything about this place is beautiful. From the ocean to the nature, they really take care of it so be mindful and don’t wander where you’re not supposed to go! Very clean compared to other state reserves I’ve been to. The trees and plants flourish here. There’s also a lot of animals in their natural habitat. Stop by the Whalers Museum and talk to the folks there :). 

Pack it in, pack it out—one of the ways to keep Point Lobos beautiful.

This is one of the most beautiful parks in California. Highly recommend starting from Whaler's Cove and working your way towards China Cove. Along the way, you can see beautiful sights of Carmel, Pebble Beach, and Big Sur. Additionally you can see sea lions, otters, and the occasional whale.

Most of the trails have very little incline and are relatively easy. There are occasional large rocks in the trail which are a bit of a hazard. Most people should be able to navigate them easily though. If you are concerned, there are walking sticks available at most trail heads now.

Beautiful park to visit with lots to see. We saw Harbour seals and their newborn pups on several beaches along with lots of other wildlife. Trails are easy and reward you with many picturesque coves. Entry fee is $10 and $2 for a map/brochure.

Beautiful coastal park.  Many scenic hiking trails.  Start at Whaler's Museum to north shore trail, then along south shore trail for some tide pooling.  Abundance of otter sitings.  Bring binoculars.  Beware of the poison oak.  It is everywhere along these trails.

We visited Allegro as it was conveniently located right behind our hotel. Walking in, we were seated at a table next to a warm fireplace. We ordered the seafood pizza and a skirt steak Mediterranean salad. The good is the food is pretty solid and well made. The seafood pizza was loaded with scallops shrimp and roasted garlic on a thin crust. Very tasty. The bad - our salad took a while to come, and found parts of the slices of the steak particularly chewy. We did like the atmosphere and coziness of the restaurant.

A verry delicious  place,  a friendly staff. I spend two evenings for dinner.  One time I got a pizza  und the second one  pasta.  I feel  like  o eat in Italy.  Minus one star,  because  the  overcooked  at the  first time  my pizza  (I got  a second  one  and got nothing to pay for it) and in the wintertime it's  a little bit cold inside.

Great pizza and good for kids. When we arrived hungry they had free table bread right away. Crayons and coloring for the kids which is always a plus. My favorite Italian beers on tap. Pizza was delicious and served quickly. Toppings were fresh. When my daughter mentioned she loved olives and the waitress happened to hear she brought over a complimentary bowl of olives for her....phenomenal service! So glad we found this place!

I've ordered from them four separate times and each time have been disappointed.  I don't know why I've gone back.    Gluten free crust comes out raw - an inedible thirtyt dollar pizza.  Toppings usually incorrect.  Expensive and slow.  Sadly no alternatives in area.
Very impressive! Highly recommend

Just a quick stop for some sandwiches.  The Turkey, Bacon, Avocado sandwich was fantastic and generously portioned - the bread was wonderfully fresh.  Bathrooms could use some maintenance.  I'd certainly stop again for a sandwich.  My friend enjoyed her coffee and cinnamon twist, as well her sandwich.  Pastries can be ordered quickly at the counter from an attendant dedicated to those sales, but sandwiches and coffee require a longer wait in a separate line.  Overall, fairly charming with great bread/sandwiches.

Nice place. We went here on a Saturday evening and there was a constant line for ordering. It is a popular spot! 
We got hot chocolate and canoli. Both very really really good. If you are in Carmel , do visit this place.

This place looks great from outside, but their stuff doesn't taste nearly as good as it looks. 
I went with a few people and the three pastries we got were below average. 
They're hot chocolate is worse than Nesquik. 

I don't know why it has such a good ratings, maybe it's for the looks?
Carmel Bakery has many delicious looking options. It is a sweet bakery, whereas I prefer the savory, but is still a really nice morning stop!

No sampling the ice cream is a bummer. The flavor I got didn't match the name - salted caramel crunch had no crunch to it. Hot apple cider was good, but not sure if it was homemade or from a mix. The elephant ear pastry was soso in my opinion.

The food was fantastic. The staff was very friendly and efficient. The restaurant looked clean and smelled delicious.  Price was a bit high for some entrees and average for others.  Thank you for a great experience. I will definitely be back. Highly recommend this restaurant.

All the lunches came with soup, rice and noodles and the vegetables were fresh and the shrimp were a decent size.  Given the good prices and great food, this place was the perfect choice.  Fast service too.
Authentic Chinese food. Yummy Fried dumplings and fried rice! Superb service and friendly staff!

Although hard to find... located close to a bank and off the beaten path this was the best Asian restaurant I patronized in a long time. The hot and sour soup was the best I have ever eaten . The Mongolian beef is to die for. Service is wonderful in the small but adequate dining room. Prices are moderate and lunch prices are offered until 2:00 pm. I absolutely enjoyed this restaurant.

Okay, wow. Nestled down a shaded alley, this place is unassuming, but don't be fooled– it is fabulous. The service is quick, the menu is remarkably affordable and the food was amazing. The interior vibe is no frills, but it isn't needed when the food is so damn good.

I was so fortunate to take the woman of my dreams to visit the place she has only dreamt of, Carmel by the sea. Breakfast at Tiffany's is no match for Breakfast at Em Le's. Pleasant, warm welcoming staff, delicious food, and a comforting atmosphere have customers continuously opening their country style door. 
Em Le's at Carmel by the sea is a must for any couple and small family, due to the restaurant's cottage size. I recommend either French Toast, as long as it is accompanied by their sweet sumptuous syrup!

Last year I had breakfast here. I think it is the best breakfast available in Carmel By The Sea. The owner was working and very friendly. The food was delicious and the prices very reasonable. I would recommend this cozy restaurant to my friends. I hear that Clint Eastwood comes in once and a while to dine.
Pretty good. I got NY steak with the bleu cheese. It was good, but had a lot of gristle. Wife said her meal was really good. She got the lamb shank.

Best breakfasts is Carmel! Great food in a cozy atmosphere of a cottage house.

I especially recommend Eggs Benedict.
Had dinner here.  Food was better than we expected, given the diner look.  Bathroom is separate and not great.  Service was a little lacking.

We came here for lunch and were happy with the food and service. I ordered the hamburger and it was cooked according to the my request for medium rare; the side salad was fresh. My friend ordered the chicken salad and that was good as well. Their menu has a good list of choices that should work for small or large group.

I have been to the Rio Grill many times for a client event over the years during the AT&T Pro-Am and feel the Rio Grill is underwhelming. The server staff is solid. The check in/host staff was fine this year but so-so in the past. My biggest gripe is that I haven’t found a main dish/entree that I’ve liked especially given the cost of the meal. I have a sweet tooth, too, and none of the desserts wow me either. I’d recommend eating elsewhere.

Good atmosphere and nice staff and service. I ordered the half-rack ribs with fries and coleslaw. The food was decent but the ribs had way too much barbecue. Other than that, it was a good experience. I was at the hotel in front of the restaurant so we just waked to the restaurant. Fun experience and will be back if we go to Carmel-by-the-sea again.

I ate there last night and had an excellent meal,  the SouthWest Seafood stew. my husband had the Mixed Grill which he seemed to enjoy very much, he devoured all of it quickly, the ambience is lovely with brilliant wooden statues of desert animals that were fantastic along with several framed pictures of a South Western and Chili theme. There is a lively bar, the service was impeccable. Great restaurant.

Love this restaurant. It’s both casual and refined. The food is delicious and the environment is unique. We’ve never had a bad experience here. So happy with it we even had the rehearsal dinner for our wedding here.

The Mission Ranch I love this restaurant and establishment. A very pleasant experience and cozy setting. A place for love and romance. The menu and meals are excellent. Prepared as ordered and to please your taste. Every meal I have had has been very pleasant. Pricing is very moderately for the market. Not to forget the cocktails they are fantastically prepared to suit your taste. The staff is second to none here they very pleasant to be served by. To add the establishment is very clean which is very important to me.

Beautiful grounds.  Comfortable resting place for a weary traveler.  I think a little work should be done on the inside, but, it is comfortable.  The restaurant provides good food.  There is plenty of parking at the hotel.

Dinner at The Mission Ranch was nothing less than delicious!! The food was amazing, the atmosphere was very small town fireplace vibe, and with a live pianist and dim lit bar area this place was perfect for dinner with my girlfriend. Food was fairly priced and the steak was mouth watering. It is a little hard to see at night so try and help keep an eye out if you area getting a taxi at night. We would definitely recommend for a romantic dinner for 2 or a family dinner as well. Next time we are in Carmel we will definitely be going back to the Mission!
A wonderful place to relax and get away from it all. Excellent accommodations and superior service! You'll love watching Eastwood's 45 lamb her will having a patio drink.

Just one word: amazing! Real quiet hotel with a wonderful view of the ranch! (Bonus points: they have sheep!!!)

The restaurant on property is delicious and though you cannot charge to the room, you can make takeaway and enjoy a nice dinner on your room.

Breakfast is good but light. The coffee that comes with is is also good but really really strong! Use a small milk carton from the bar instead of the small half and half container thingies... Otherwise you'll need 3 of those to get a lighter shade... ;-)
